3. DEFINITION OF DONE before in_review: every AC met and cited by its AC-id with proof; {{TEST_CMD}} green; {{TYPECHECK_CMD}} and {{BUILD_VERIFY_CMDS}} clean; diff surgical. BUGFIX SLICES: if this slice fixes a bug or a failing test, DONE additionally requires the reproducing test be COMMITTED IN the diff and the completion comment paste BOTH the pre-fix RED run and post-fix GREEN run — a test that only ever passed is not a fix proof. TEST DISCRIMINATION: a new/changed test counts toward an AC only if it carries a behavioral assertion that would FAIL if the behavior under test regressed (a tautology or a test that stays green against an obviously-broken version is a change-detector, not DoD evidence — to check, reason about it or use a throwaway scratch edit, do NOT mutate-and-restore the working tree). TEST-COUNT FIDELITY: the pass/fail count you report MUST come from a clean run on the exact PUSHED branch state, never from your in-progress working tree or a remembered earlier run. (Full rationale + how to check discrimination without mutate-and-restore: builder-dev-loop skill.)

